The paper discusses the design of a user interface for a mobile augmented reality application for military applications. This involves managing information in a useful and usable manner, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses methods for presenting information that represents entities occluded from the user's view, which falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of augmented reality technology is also relevant to the category of augmented reality (cs.AR). The paper also discusses collaboration with other mobile users and/or a command center, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
